        <section id="partners">
            <h2>Join the Movement</h2>
            <p>ReSmokle isn’t just a business—it’s a revolution in responsibility. We're inviting conscious consumers, visionary partners, bold sponsors, and forward-thinking investors to be part of something bigger. Together, we can reshape an overlooked waste stream into a force for environmental impact, community empowerment, and economic innovation. Whether you want to clean your pipe, support sustainable practices, co-create new recycling solutions, or back a first-to-market idea with massive growth potential—ReSmokle is your opportunity to act. Let’s Reuse. Recycle. ReImagine… and rebuild a cleaner future, one piece at a time.</p>
            <h3>The Hidden Waste of Vaping and Smoking</h3>
            <p>The vaping and smoking industries generate a disproportionately large waste stream relative to the size of their products. A single vape cartridge weighs less than half an ounce, yet it's often sold in packaging that weighs up to ten times more—made from mixed materials like hard plastic, metal, rubber, and cardboard that are rarely recycled. With over 9 million adult e-cigarette users in the U.S. alone, this adds up to millions of pounds of non-biodegradable waste annually. Most of it ends up in landfills—or worse, in waterways and neighborhoods—because standard recycling systems aren't equipped to handle these specialized materials. This growing imbalance between product and packaging creates an urgent environmental and waste management issue, one that ReSmokle is determined to solve through targeted collection, responsible processing, and meaningful reuse.</p>
